Author: Liza Carvelli
Name: Questionable
Description:
A tiny little quest helper plugin, which does quests for you automatically where possible. Uses navmesh to automatically walk to all quest waypoints, and tries to automatically complete all steps along the way (excluding dungeons, single player duties and combat).

Not all quests are supported, check the discord or git repository for an up-to-date list.

Required Plugins: vnavmesh, TextAdvance, Lifestream
Punchline: A tiny quest helper plugin.
Changelog:
v2.6 (2024-08-11)
No longer in testing, quick recap of changes from 2.0 to 2.5:

- More quests (Moonfire Faire thanks to JerryWester, Qitari unlock)
- Add support for gathering quests
- Add Endwalker studium deliveries
- Add gathering/turning in weekly delivery items for Zhloe, M'naago, Kurenai and Adkiragh
- Add gathering leves (one level 90 & 96 leve for MIN/BTN right now)
- Lots of smaller fixes, including to quest paths

Changes for this version from the previous testing version (2.5):

- Add mini quest window that only shows quest name + minimal buttons
- Add Crystal Tower quests as priority quests
- Add supported class/job quests as priority quests
- Add Shadowbringers role quests as priority quests until you've completed one quest line
- Show priority quests as 'next quest' if you can't currently progress in MSQ (instead of the unaccepted next MSQ quest) if some aren't completed
- Improve handling of quest automation, remove 'automatically accept next quest' checkbox
- Interactions now check that you've been occupied for at least one frame and will retry if not
- Update ARR quest paths
- Fix Questionable no longer working properly on any quest, if the next MSQ quest is 'A Time to Every Purpose' and you haven't finished the Crystal Tower quests
- Automatically close the other half of ARR credits that wasn't closed automatically yet
- Don't unmount to use Vesper Bay aetheryte tickets as it's not necessary
- Use mount after using a Vesper Bay aetheryte tickets if on foot
- Add 'EquipRecommended' task

v2.5 (testing only) (2024-08-09)
- Add Moonfire Faire (2024) quests, thanks to JerryWester
- Automatically close levemete menu after a leve has been turned in
- Fix functionality for auto-accepting leve rewards accidentally also affecting quests
- Minor updates to ARR paths
- Add extra UI elements to be considered as loading screens/occupied

v2.4 (testing only) (2024-08-08)
- Add "Vestiges of War" (Yak T'el, Lv. 96) as proof-of-concept for gathering leves
- Partially revert target-related changes for interactions
- Improve logic for skipping gathering nodes when all possible candidates are in render distance but not targetable

v2.3 (testing only) (2024-08-07)
- Ensure you have enough inventory slots for gathering collectables
- Add BTN 65-70 class quests
- Add Qitari unlock quests
- Attempt to fix auto questing for the MSQ sometimes stopping

v2.2 (testing only) (2024-08-05)
- Add automatic turn-in of custom deliveries for custom delivery clients
- Rework how gathering tasks are handled internally
- (dev only) Validate that dialogue choices are referring to valid excel sheets/keys

Author: The Combat Reborn Team
Name: Rotation Solver Reborn
Description:
Analyses combat information every frame and finds the best action.

This means almost all the information available in one frame in combat, including the status of all players in the party, the status of any hostile targets, skill cooldowns, the MP and HP of characters, the location of characters, casting status of the hostile target, combo, combat duration, player level, etc.
Then, it will highlight the best action on the hot bar, or help you to click on it.
It is designed for `general combat`, not for savage or ultimate. Use it carefully.
Punchline: Analyses combat information every frame and finds the best action.
Changelog:

Author: daemitus, kawaii
Name: Yes Already
Punchline: Clicks Yes in various dialogs you've specified.
Description: Tired of clicking yes in Praetorium? Can't stand using keys in dungeons? Well do I have the plugin for you! Yes Already is specifically designed to click all the annoying dialogs you've grown accustomed facerolling. Just enter the dialog text, and you'll never see it again! Also works with /regex/ and has several built-in modules for dialogs that aren't quite yes/no prompts but act like it (like desynth).
